ctWANMuxMaxNumGroups.name: ctWANMuxMaxNumGroups
ctWANMuxMaxNumGroups.description: Get the maximum number of Inverse Multiplexer groups allowed to be programmed for this device. This value is the number of physical WAN connections, divided by the minimum number of channels for a single mux to be operational (2). However, some devices may only support a single inverse multiplexer group.

ctWanMuxAdmin.name: ctWanMuxAdmin
ctWanMuxAdmin.description: Used to enable and disable the Inverse Multiplexer Application. This object is used to enable/disable Inverse Multiplexing for the entire device. Inverse Multiplexer Groups may be enabled/disabled independently using ctWanMuxGroupAdmin. This object must be set to enabled for any inverse multiplexing to occur on the device.

ctWanMuxGroupTable.name: ctWanMuxGroupTable
ctWanMuxGroupTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters of one of the Inverse Multiplexer groups.

ctWanMuxGroupEntry.name: ctWanMuxGroupEntry
ctWanMuxGroupEntry.description: A description of a single Inverse Multiplexer group entry.

ctWanMuxGroupId.name: ctWanMuxGroupId
ctWanMuxGroupId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of groups which belong to the WAN Inverse Multiplexer. This value ranges from 1 to the maximum number of programmable groups as described by ctWANMuxMaxNumGroups.

ctWanMuxGroupAdmin.name: ctWanMuxGroupAdmin
ctWanMuxGroupAdmin.description: Used to enable and disable an Inverse Multiplexer group which evenly distributes data traffic in a properly sequenced fashion, over two or more single channel Wide Area Network connections such as DS1, E1, DDS, or SYNC. Each of the single channel connections must be configured with an appropriate datalink protocol. A minimum of two channels, each assigned to it's own physical interface, is required before the Inverse Multiplexer group can be enabled.

ctWanMuxGroupNumChannels.name: ctWanMuxGroupNumChannels
ctWanMuxGroupNumChannels.description: Get the number of channels currently associated with this Inverse Multiplexer group. A minimum of two channels, each assigned to it's own physical interface, is required before the Inverse Multiplexer group can be enabled.

ctWanMuxGroupAddChannel.name: ctWanMuxGroupAddChannel
ctWanMuxGroupAddChannel.description: Add a channel to the channel list used by this Inverse Multiplexer group. Before a channel is added, the channel must be assigned a MIB II ifindex, and an acceptable Datalink Protocol. When this object is set, it is set with the ifindex value. This object is always read as a 1.

ctWanMuxGroupDelChannel.name: ctWanMuxGroupDelChannel
ctWanMuxGroupDelChannel.description: Delete a channel to the channel list used by this Inverse Multiplexer group. Before a channel is deleted, the channel must exist in the Inverse Multiplexer group's channel table. When this object is set, it is set with the ifindex value of the channel the user wishes to delete from the channel table. This object is always read as a 1.

ctWanMuxChannelTable.name: ctWanMuxChannelTable
ctWanMuxChannelTable.description: Table containing ifindex values, representing WAN channels, used by the Inverse Multiplexer. The table also contains statistics reported about each channel.

ctWanMuxChannelEntry.name: ctWanMuxChannelEntry
ctWanMuxChannelEntry.description: A description of a single entry.

ctWanMuxChannelGroupId.name: ctWanMuxChannelGroupId
ctWanMuxChannelGroupId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of groups which belong to the WAN Inverse Multiplexer. This value ranges from 1 to the maximum number of programmable groups as described by ctWANMuxMaxNumGroups.

ctWanMuxChannelId.name: ctWanMuxChannelId
ctWanMuxChannelId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of member channel ifindex values which belong to a WAN Inverse Multiplexer group.

ctWanMuxChannelIfIndex.name: ctWanMuxChannelIfIndex
ctWanMuxChannelIfIndex.description: Returns an ifindex associated with a WAN channel used for Inverse Multiplexing.

ctWanMuxChannelPhysNum.name: ctWanMuxChannelPhysNum
ctWanMuxChannelPhysNum.description: Returns a unique physical connection identifier associated with this channel's physical WAN connection.

ctWanMuxChannelBwAvail.name: ctWanMuxChannelBwAvail
ctWanMuxChannelBwAvail.description: Returns a value which represents the available bandwidth for transmitting data existing for the physical WAN connection associated with this channel. The value is represented in bits/sec.

ctWanMuxChannelByteCount.name: ctWanMuxChannelByteCount
ctWanMuxChannelByteCount.description: Returns a value which represents a cumulative count of bytes transmitted out from this interface. The count includes any bytes transmitted across the physical medium, less physical medium framing.

ctWanMuxChannelStatus.name: ctWanMuxChannelStatus
ctWanMuxChannelStatus.description: Returns the current status of the channel associated with an inverse multiplexer group. The channel is active when the group admin status is enabled, and the channel is operational. The channel is inactive when either the group admin status is disabled, or the channel is not operational.
